modules.description: Handles incoming WebSocket connections asynchronously. Accepts a configuration, error handler, and input handler generator, then creates a deferred unit after establishing a connection. Useful for building event-driven WebSocket servers that process client messages with custom logic.

Connects to a WebSocket server with specified host, port, and resource, handling errors and incoming messages through provided callbacks. Works with WebSocket connections and asynchronous sockets, enabling bidirectional communication over HTTP Upgrade. Useful for implementing real-time clients that interact with WebSocket-based APIs or services.

This module provides asynchronous WebSocket server and client implementations. The server handles incoming connections with custom error and message handling logic, while the client establishes connections to WebSocket endpoints and manages bidirectional communication. It works with asynchronous sockets and WebSocket protocols, enabling real-time services like chat applications or live data feeds.
